result.formatted_address: 11 Man Kwong St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Hong Kong Maritime Museum

reviews.text: This is one of my favorite museums in the world. Great for a rainy day and excellent place for a kid-friendly outing. They have high-quality and interactive exhibits. Highly recommend!

Much more in depth and interesting than expected with a thorough history of the way Hong Kong has been used as a port town for centuries, and a really nice integration of the multi-cultural and colonial history of the city. The exhibits span from the beginning of the opium trade to the very modern renovations if the docks and wharfs today. Honestly, I think it's a must see in HK. Also it has a FANTASTIC viewing deck and fixed binoculars.
It's a good place to explore and interactive things for the children. There is a boat simulator but only at weekends and PH. It's $30 for adult and $15 for children. Nice views of the harbour too.
For its low price, it gives a good exhibition on the history of navigation in China and the development of Hong Kong as a seaport. Plenty of beautiful models of various kinds of ships.

Great little museum in the core of Central. We went when there was an exhibition on the Pirates of Hong Kong. There was in parallel an art exhibit on saving the sharks. There are permanent exhibitions of which many are interactive. Only to name a few: radar, waves, weather and a history of sea exploration e. G. A scaphandre which can be tried on.  Information is available in Mandarin and English.

result.adr_address: 香港中環民光街11號
result.name: 香港海事博物館

reviews.text: 意外にと言ってはなんだが、博物館としてだけでなく、船の科学館的にも充実した展示。船の模型が盛りだくさんで、その筋の人ならなおうれしいのでは。場所的に、わざわざ目的地にせずとも、スターフェリーに乗るついでにちょうどいい。解説は中国語および英語のみ。中に操船のシミュレータ的なものがあるが、入場料とは別料金。

amusing....se si ha tempo vale la visita.L'Hong Kong Maritime Museum è un'istituzione educativa senza fini di lucro finanziata dalla comunità marittima internazionale e dal governo di Hong Kong. Si trova al Central Pier 8, Hong Kong. Il museo è stato riaperto al pubblico nel febbraio 2013.
